						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/Commodities/Biofuels/Related-developments/Unique-rainforest-fungus-makes-bio-hydrocarbons-including-diesel-from-cellulose" title="Unique rainforest fungus makes bio-hydrocarbons, including diesel from cellulose" alt="link">Unique rainforest fungus makes bio-hydrocarbons, including diesel from cellulose</a></h2>

	
					<p>A unique fungus that makes diesel compounds has been discovered living in trees in the rainforest. The fungus is potentially a totally new source of green energy and scientists are now working to develop its fuel producing potential. The fungus, which has been named Gliocladium roseum, produces a number of different molecules made of hydrogen and carbon that are found in diesel (Source: Biopact, 06 November 2008). </p>
							<p><span class="date">1/12/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
